Podcast via https://theblockchainsocialist.com/otns-cosmo-localism-beyonders-and-the-medieval-parallels-to-digital-nomadism/

=Description=

"With Michel Bauwens, founder of the P2P Foundation. We discuss his concept of cosmo-localism which advocates for everything heavy to be local, and everything light to be global, how many medieval institutions were cosmo-local, and the implications of the rise of knowledge workers detached from physical territory."

